Text.string: I've got another Clapslist mission ready to go!
Time to help a xenogeologist!
I spent years searching for Brownrock samples, and barely scraped together my prized collection. Please find my beautiful specimens!
Damn... chill, man. It's just a rock.
Okay, you're very high strung about these rocks, you know that?
You are overly agitated. It is only a rock. Calm yourself.
All right, boyo. It's still just a rock. Calm down already.

These are more than rocks, dammit! They're my whole world! They're all I have! They're even named after me! “139.377 Brown Rocks”—or, “Brownrock” for short. Although they're actually quite an exquisite gold color! Yes, I realize this is confusing, and I don't care. Just find them!
Yeuch! Disgusting primates!
This request came from a science guy named Miles Brown who lives on Eden-6! I didn't really understand all the science words, but it sounds like he needs your help with rocks! Thrilling!
The rest of my specimens must be in there! Collect them!

Ahhhh, I see now. They're using my Brownrock specimens for decoration! Fascinating. And appalling! In related news, I hate this planet and everything that lives here. Actually, I hate everything that lives everywhere.
My word. I've spent my whole life seeking these stones, and I've never seen so many in one place!
And THAT is the biggest jabber I've ever seen! It's like their... King Jabber!
It would appear this King Jabber has been sending his underlings on endless fetch quests to gather all the Brownrock in the area. What a nightmare!
Vault Hunter! Please, help me! This is an emergency of the utmost... emergency!
All right. Spill it. What's really going on with you and these rocks?
There is something weird going on here, okay? Time to fess up!
There is a strangeness here that demands explanation!
Okay, friend, what's REALLY goin' on with you and them rocks?
Fine! Fine, you've caught me. I'll spill the beans. I am utterly enthralled by the transformation of the Brownrocks' calcite during recrystallization which causes a unique form of foliation banding.
That's it?
That's all?
That is all?
Annnd?
Why, it's positively scandalous for a man in my position to be so enamored by this process. Don't you see?
Uh, no.
Naye bhai.
No.
Not in the slightest!

Thank you for recovering my precious, helpless little specimens! Finally, I may continue my research. Alone. Blissfully apart from all the filthy organisms that inhabit the universe. I no longer have need of your assistance, so... bye!

Hey, recruit! Seven years ago, I started the “Clapslist” service to connect people in need with heroes like you! I... look, I forgot the password. But hey, these requests are only seven years old, so I bet these people still need help/are alive!
Sorry, it's just... living things are so disgusting. With their... skin. And orifices! Ugh, it's revolting!
We still haven't found my most-prized specimen! Keep looking!
Ohh! Please retrieve my final specimen. She's right there. I call her Abigail.
Thank goodness you've come! My babies are gone! A pack of filthy jabbers stole all of my precious baby stones!
Excellent! Now please return my sweet stones back to me!
Rock babies, huh? Putting you in the weirdo column.
You're a strange one, aren't you?
Your attachment to these stones is slightly troubling.
Baby rocks, eh? Yeah, not gonna mess with that one.
Just find those jabbers and UTTERLY EVISCERATE THOSE FILTHY ORGANISMS!
